ABC News anchor Peter Jennings has been diagnosed with lung cancer, prompting a generational shift in network news.
Despite his illness, Jennings plans to continue anchoring "World News Tonight" during treatment.
Colleagues express sadness and support for the iconic anchor.
Viewers value the strong bond they have with Jennings, who has led the newscast for 22 years.
ABC executives assure that Jennings remains the anchor, but plans for a successor are being considered.
Jennings' absence poses a challenge for ABC as they aim to surpass NBC Nightly News in ratings.
The news industry faces uncertainty as it navigates the transition to a new era of evening news
